br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#006400>(8/31/01 12:17:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=717.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Features - Coming Soon....</span><hr size=1> While I admit I'm not a beta tester for DAoC some of the things mentioned seem to take away from any attempt to make a game with some limits. <br>
An example of that is no need to wait for mana (or what ever system they use) to regenerate. On the surface it seems to me that this is nice for people who want to play a game where there is no limitation on how many times a person may cast a spell. Personally I like the idea that mana takes time to regen in EQ. It's represtative of most systems in many of the Fantasy books you see out there. I have to wonder what has been implimented to limit a casters abilities.<br>
While it's nice that a mob that drops an a special item (the example given was Frenzy) every time, what is the spawn cycle for said mob? <br>
Spells automatically appearing when you attain the level to use them? Again it seems the creators are catering to whims of some people who want everything given to them. I like the idea there are spells you can research (let's not discuss spoiler sites since they are just that SPOILERS). Refering back to the Fantasy genre spells traditionally aren't just a given but earned in some fashion. <br>
Not sure how they plan to do melee combat but I don't look forward to 100+ fights where I'm banging away at the keys a la Street Fighter. <br>
I also like the idea of assembling a large force to take down a single target. It's a good feeling even if I don't win anything. There's a skill to co-ordinating that sort of thing and it's nice to see alot of people working together putting their personal skill into the game as well. Skills developed over a long time playing the game (sometimes too long).<br>
Some of the things do sound logical and easily implimented and I'm not sure why Sony hasn't incorporated them into EQ yet. I like the way a tank can shield a caster, self binding for all classes and the random quest generator. <br>
I'm sort of non-comittal about the lack of penalty for a death. It doesn't bother me that there is some xp loss for a death, it make some sense. <br>
<br>
Not knowing the kind of funding the creators of DAoC has I have to wonder if they can last long enough to threaten EQ. Since Mythic Entertainment isn't a large company people have to wonder if they have enough capital to last until the growing stages are past and hit the break even point. They are a relativly small player in the market and in these days of venture capital drying up they might not last. A good concept just isn't enough to survive in the software world, OS/2 is a great expample of that. The area of on line games is still growing but I'm not sure the rate of growth matches the needs some of a small company like this. Faced with the juggernaughts of Sony and Microsoft they might just fade away. Personally I'd like to see some competition out there just to keep Sony on their toes. Maybe they'll hire some more Customer Service reps instead of letting that aspect of the business lag.<br>
<br>
Warasen Durendel<br>
53 Paladin<br>
Crimson Watchers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF8DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/udextoraldertree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dextor Aldertree</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Keeper of Rants<br>MMDN Editorials Editor<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/staff.gif></span><br>  Posts: 457<br> <font color=#006400>(8/31/01 12:53:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=717.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Features - Coming Soon....</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Personally I like the idea that mana takes time to regen in EQ. It's represtative of most systems in many of the Fantasy books you see out there.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Staring at a spellbook is entertainment? Remind yourself never to ask for clarity from here on. Mana regen is supposed to take time you know. And exactly what do fantasy books have to do with any of this? Who said that the genre had to follow some template created 50 years ago?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> While it's nice that a mob that drops an a special item (the example given was Frenzy) every time, what is the spawn cycle for said mob?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
No idea, but again, what's it matter? The idea is to create a game where items are not the center of attention. In DAoC, stuff breaks down with use. That &quot;Blade of Uberness&quot; might be good the day you get it. But eventually, it's going to break and then what? Life goes on, that's what. Play the game, don't let it play you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Refering back to the Fantasy genre spells traditionally aren't just a given but earned in some fashion.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
What about the priest classes in Baldur's Gate? All spells available to them are automatically available upon reaching a new level. Even in D&amp;D, you can pretty much choose what spells you want. Again, the idea is to get your butt out there and play, not spend time searching spoiler sites for the locations of much-needed spells. And with DAoC, each caster class can specilize in different areas of magic. Cleric #1 might choose to excel in offensive magic, while Cleric #2 chooses to concentrate more in healing and buffing. Again, the game is there to be played and not vice versa.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Not sure how they plan to do melee combat but I don't look forward to 100+ fights where I'm banging away at the keys a la Street Fighter.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Who said you would? DAoC isn't going to use twitch combat anymore than EQ. (Which, btw, consists of nothing more than continuously clicking attack, bash, and kick until someone dies.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I also like the idea of assembling a large force to take down a single target. It's a good feeling even if I don't win anything. There's a skill to co-ordinating that sort of thing and it's nice to see alot of people working together putting their personal skill into the game as well.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
3 groups of 8 isn't a large force? If not, participate in the realm battles where one team attempts to go deep into enemy territory and capture a realm artifact. How does 50 people trying to take over a highly populated and defended fort sound? (And the enemy is PC and not NPC.) You want tactics and strategy and coordination? DAoC is going to have it in spades.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I'm sort of non-comittal about the lack of penalty for a death. It doesn't bother me that there is some xp loss for a death, it make some sense.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
From what I understand, you do lose some XP when you die, in addition to a smidgen of constitution. The constitution loss can be regained through either praying at your gravesite, or by visiting a priest. (I'm fuzzy on this since it was never of any real interest to me.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Not knowing the kind of funding the creators of DAoC has I have to wonder if they can last long enough to threaten EQ. Since Mythic Entertainment isn't a large company people have to wonder if they have enough capital to last until the growing stages are past and hit the break even point. They are a relativly small player in the market and in these days of venture capital drying up they might not last.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Vivendi Universal Publishing is the name of the company that's going to manufacture, market, and distribute DAoC. (Vivendi also does the same thing for Blizzard, makers of Diablo and Starcraft.) In addition to that, a deal has been reached with Dimension/Miramax to develop and produce a television series based on DAoC. So like I've already said, don't automatically assume that Mythic is going to be a &quot;small player&quot; in the market of online PC gaming.  Big bad Sony doesn't exactly scare people like they'd want you to believe.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEEFDE><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uminahmorningdew.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minah Morningdew</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Defender<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif></span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#006400>(8/31/01 2:30:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=717.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://minahtrueheart.homestead.com/files/mars69.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Features - Coming Soon....</span><hr size=1> I was accepted tp DAoC beta 4 two days ago . Took me a day to download it all . <br>
