<br>
As to death penalties, there is a penalty.  There always is.  However, you can /decide/ how bad it will be.  If you don't have time/don't want to wait around for a rez, you release your corpse and return to your bind point with all your stuff.  I believe then that you can go back to your tombstone and pray to get back some of your xp.   Clerics can give you back lost constitution. <br>
<br>
As to graphics, well, if your underlying engine is a good one, you can always spend time on graphics later.  They're graphics are pretty rocking for when they started development.  Like Verant keeps saying, at some point you just have to draw the line and work with what you've got or you never get anywhere. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
